<subSubSection pageId="23" pageNumber="24" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="23.[151,1436,150,213]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,150,176]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species is named in honor of Lajos Vári and Georg van Son, well-known South African lepidopterologists and former curators of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[575,710,186,212]" class="Insecta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="order">Lepidoptera</taxonomicName>
at the TMSA, who collected the 
<typeStatus box="[1081,1179,186,212]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">holotype</typeStatus>
of new species.
</paragraph>
